ll,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct description is that the basilic vein \u003Cstrong\u003Eruns along the medial side of the arm\u003C/strong\u003E. It is a superficial vein that eventually drains into the brachial vein, which then contributes to the formation of the axillary vein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELocated on the lateral side of the arm\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes the cephalic vein, not the basilic vein\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDrains into the cephalic vein\u003C/strong\u003E - The basilic vein does not drain into the cephalic vein\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EForms the axillary vein directly\u003C/strong\u003E - The basilic vein drains into the brachial vein, which then forms the axillary vein\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELocated deep to the brachial artery\u003C/strong\u003E - The basilic vein is superficial, not deep\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The basilic vein is a superficial vein located in the upper limb.","It runs along the medial side of the arm and forearm.","The basilic vein drains into the brachial vein, forming part of the deep venous system."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66189"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18120"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66189","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66189"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-23T12:12:24+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-23T12:12:55+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10834"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80866"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4926"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiovascular","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:14:59